The paper proposes a method for query answering over knowledge graphs using embeddings and message passing. This involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) such as embedding learning and scoring entities, as well as from databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) for handling graph structures and learning models. The paper also discusses natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as related fields.
